author: dblevins
msg: Improved Options support so that all properties that accept a Set of enum values now automatically accept ALL and NONE to have an easy way for users to imply those values without us having to add NONE or ALL enum items explicitly which leads to strange code.
Additionally TRUE is an alias for ALL and FALSE an alias for NONE.  This allows options that used to support only true/false values to be further defined in the future without breaking compatibility.
